                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="50293" author="bogl" created="Thu, 10 Jan 2013 17:02:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing due to customer request.  Problem was due to a feature of the customer&apos;s environment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50292" author="jaylan" created="Thu, 10 Jan 2013 16:59:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem indeed was caused by our version of mpirun_rsh. Please close this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49983" author="jaylan" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 19:52:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same problem still occured in a clean sles11sp2 environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will look into the mpirun_rsh next.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49965" author="jaylan" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 14:06:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I started to suspect it was caused by running sles11sp2 kernel in an sles11sp1 environment. I do not have an sles11sp2 image to image my test system, so I installed sles11sp2 kernel in an sles11sp1 environment. This maybe a compatibility issue between the kernel and run-time libraries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will post when I have more information.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49921" author="jaylan" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 21:13:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will look into it tomorrow. I originally thought the &quot;bind: Address family not supported by protocol&quot; came from write_disjoint binary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49918" author="bogl" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 20:49:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jay, from the log you&apos;ve posted the command that&apos;s failing is mpirun_rsh.  That doesn&apos;t seem to be part of openmpi.  I can&apos;t find it anywhere.  Is this something specific to your environment?  Is it a script that invokes mpirun with some options?  Without knowing more about it I can&apos;t figure out what it&apos;s complaining about.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49914" author="pjones" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 20:19:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
